28ns_sortlisttype_t
29ns_sortlist_setup(dns_acl_t *acl, dns_aclenv_t *env,
30 isc_netaddr_t *clientaddr, const void **argp)
31{
32 unsigned int i;
33
34 if (acl == NULL)
35 goto dont_sort;
36
37 for (i = 0; i < acl->length; i++) {
38 /*
39 * 'e' refers to the current 'top level statement'
40 * in the sortlist (see ARM).
41 */
42 dns_aclelement_t *e = &acl->elements[i];
43 dns_aclelement_t *try_elt;
44 dns_aclelement_t *order_elt = NULL;
45 const dns_aclelement_t *matched_elt = NULL;
46
47 if (e->type == dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl) {
48 dns_acl_t *inner = e->nestedacl;
49
50 if (inner->length == 0)
51 try_elt = e;
52 else if (inner->length > 2)
53 goto dont_sort;
54 else if (inner->elements[0].negative)
55 goto dont_sort;
56 else {
57 try_elt = &inner->elements[0];
58 if (inner->length == 2)
59 order_elt = &inner->elements[1];
60 }
61 } else {
62 /*
63 * BIND 8 allows bare elements at the top level
64 * as an undocumented feature.
65 */
66 try_elt = e;
67 }
68
69 if (dns_aclelement_match(clientaddr, NULL, try_elt,
70 env, &matched_elt))
71 {
72 if (order_elt != NULL) {
73 if (order_elt->type ==
74 dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl)
75 {
76 *argp = order_elt->nestedacl;
77 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_2ELEMENT);
78 } else if (order_elt->type ==
79 dns_aclelementtype_localhost &&
80 env->localhost != NULL)
81 {
82 *argp = env->localhost;
83 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_2ELEMENT);
84 } else if (order_elt->type ==
85 dns_aclelementtype_localnets &&
86 env->localnets != NULL)
87 {
88 *argp = env->localnets;
89 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_2ELEMENT);
90 } else {
91 /*
92 * BIND 8 allows a bare IP prefix as
93 * the 2nd element of a 2-element
94 * sortlist statement.
95 */
96 *argp = order_elt;
97 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_1ELEMENT);
98 }
99 } else {
100 INSIST(matched_elt != NULL);
101 *argp = matched_elt;
102 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_1ELEMENT);
103 }
104 }
105 }
106
107 /* No match; don't sort. */
108 dont_sort:
109 *argp = NULL;
110 return (NS_SORTLISTTYPE_NONE);
111}
112
113int
114ns_sortlist_addrorder2(const isc_netaddr_t *addr, const void *arg) {
115 const dns_sortlist_arg_t *sla = (const dns_sortlist_arg_t *) arg;
116 const dns_aclenv_t *env = sla->env;
117 const dns_acl_t *sortacl = sla->acl;
118 int match;
119
120 (void)dns_acl_match(addr, NULL, sortacl, env, &match, NULL);
121 if (match > 0) {
122 return (match);
123 } else if (match < 0) {
124 return (INT_MAX - (-match));
125 } else {
126 return (INT_MAX / 2);
127 }
128}
129
130int
131ns_sortlist_addrorder1(const isc_netaddr_t *addr, const void *arg) {
132 const dns_sortlist_arg_t *sla = (const dns_sortlist_arg_t *) arg;
133 const dns_aclenv_t *env = sla->env;
134 const dns_aclelement_t *element = sla->element;
135
136 if (dns_aclelement_match(addr, NULL, element, env, NULL)) {
137 return (0);
138 }
139
140 return (INT_MAX);
141}
142
143void
144ns_sortlist_byaddrsetup(dns_acl_t *sortlist_acl, dns_aclenv_t *env,
145 isc_netaddr_t *client_addr,
146 dns_addressorderfunc_t *orderp, const void **argp)
147{
148 ns_sortlisttype_t sortlisttype;
149
150 sortlisttype = ns_sortlist_setup(sortlist_acl, env, client_addr, argp);
151
152 switch (sortlisttype) {
153 case NS_SORTLISTTYPE_1ELEMENT:
154 *orderp = ns_sortlist_addrorder1;
155 break;
156 case NS_SORTLISTTYPE_2ELEMENT:
157 *orderp = ns_sortlist_addrorder2;
158 break;
159 case NS_SORTLISTTYPE_NONE:
160 *orderp = NULL;
161 break;
162 default:
163 UNEXPECTED_ERROR(__FILE__, __LINE__,
164 "unexpected return from ns_sortlist_setup(): "
165 "%d", sortlisttype);
166 break;
167 }
168}
